claims:
13. A method for producing a biologically active heterologous polypeptide in a host cell comprising: 
a) culturing host cells in a culture medium, wherein the host cells comprise both the nucleic acid molecule of claim 1 and a second nucleic acid molecule that encodes a heterologous polypeptide which comprises at least two disulfide bonds in its native form; 
b) expressing the nucleic acid molecule of claim 1 and the second nucleic acid molecule in the host cells under conditions effective to produce the chimeric polypeptide of claim 1, and the heterologous polypeptide and; 
c) isolating the heterologous polypeptide.
